# elite-clipboard

A fast, intelligent clipboard manager for Linux built entirely in Go.
Runs as a silent background daemon, classifies everything you copy into
workspaces, stores it in SQLite, and surfaces it through a native GUI,
a CLI, and an fzf fuzzy picker.

No Electron. No Python. No cloud.

---

## Platform

| Requirement    | Details                             |
|----------------|-------------------------------------|
| OS             | Linux                               |
| Display Server | X11 (Wayland not yet supported)     |
| Tested On      | Pop!_OS 22.04, Ubuntu 22.04+        |
| Architecture   | amd64                               |

---

## Stack

| Component       | Technology                    |
|-----------------|-------------------------------|
| Language        | Go 1.22+                      |
| GUI             | Fyne v2                       |
| Database        | SQLite via go-sqlite3 (CGO)   |
| Clipboard I/O   | xclip                         |
| IPC             | Unix domain socket over JSON  |
| Process manager | systemd user services         |
| Fuzzy picker    | fzf                           |

---

## Features

- Continuous background clipboard monitoring
- Auto-classification into 5 workspaces: Work, Code, Research, Temp, Sensitive
- Sensitive content detection — API keys, JWTs, credit cards, passwords redacted
- SQLite persistent storage with soft delete and pinning
- Unix socket IPC — any process can talk to the daemon
- Native GUI tray app
- Full CLI via `ecb`
- fzf fuzzy picker with copy, pin, delete bindings
- Auto-starts on login via systemd

